ient advocacy, barriers to teamwork, and the kinds of institutional and organizational efforts that remove such barriers, the health care professionals who speak in this book ultimately have one consistent message: teamwork makes patient care safer and health care careers more satisfying. These stories are an invaluable tool for those moving toward genuine interprofessional and intraprofessional teamwork.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aHealth care teams. 4aConsumer Health & Fitness. 4aMedicine & Medical Issues. 7aMEDICAL / Essays.2bisacsh  apatient care, medical sociology, medical work training, barriers of healthcare, safe patient care, interprofessional teamwork, intraprofessional teamwork.1 aAdelman, Jason, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBardes, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerguer, Ramon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBleah, Paulina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlock, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrier, Pamela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown, Theresa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurke, Kathleen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCampitelli-Thompson, Chiara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCassera, Fredrick B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChandler, Jillian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDiaper, Martyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEarly, Jessica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElliott, Adam, econ